If you are getting test output to **/out**, then you are probably running the tests as TestNG, not from the Gradle executor.   If you are doing it right, Gradle will generate a `/build` folder and you can control where your test report is generated with something like this:

    test {
        reports.html.destination = file(&quot;$buildDir/reports/gradle&quot;)
        ....

One advantage of running the tests as &quot;pure TestNG&quot; rather than using the Gradle executor, is that IntelliJ-IDEA will display to you more information about the individual test successes.   When running with Gradle, IntelliJ-IDEA is not smart enough to show you that info and so you need to rely on your test report.

