When I converted my class from Java to Kotlin, this is what converter did to runnable:

    runnable = label@ Runnable {
                    if (condition) {
                        handler!!.removeCallbacks(runnable)
                        return@label
                    }
                    if (condition) {
                        handler!!.postDelayed(runnable, 2000)
                        return@label
                    }
                   //rest of the logic here
                }

This is where the build process was throwing the above error. The reason was `return@label`

now what I did, 

    runnable = Runnable {
                        if (condition) {
                            handler!!.removeCallbacks(runnable)
                            return@Runnable
                        }
                        if (condition) {
                            handler!!.postDelayed(runnable, 2000)
                            return@Runnable
                        }
                       //rest of the logic here
                    }

now everything is super fine.
hope it will help someone!

