1. Define a task called `fatJar` in `build.gradle`:

```groovy
jar {
    baseName = &#39;base-name&#39;
    version = &#39;0.1.0&#39;
    manifest {
        attributes(
                &#39;Main-Class&#39;: &#39;com.github:&#39;
        )
    }
}

task fatJar(type: Jar) {
    manifest.from jar.manifest
//    classifier = &#39;all&#39;
    from {
        configurations.runtime.collect { it.isDirectory() ? it : zipTree(it) }
    } {
        exclude &quot;META-INF/*.SF&quot;
        exclude &quot;META-INF/*.DSA&quot;
        exclude &quot;META-INF/*.RSA&quot;
    }
    with jar
}

artifacts {
    archives fatJar
}
```

2. Run `gradle fatJar` or `./gradlew fatJar` to generate a `jar` file with all dependencies, which can run independently but may be pretty large in size (that&#39;s why it&#39;s called a fat  jar).

